TITLE: Setting Timeout in Better Fetch (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set a timeout for a fetch request using Better Fetch. It shows setting a global timeout in the createFetch options and overriding it for a specific request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/timeout-and-retry.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch } from "@better-fetch/fetch";

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "http://localhost:3000",
    timeout: 5000,
})
// ---cut---
const res = await $fetch("/api/users", {
    timeout: 10000,
});
```

