TITLE: Implementing Better Fetch Plugin Hooks
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement lifecycle hooks in a Better Fetch plugin. Includes hooks for request, response, error, and success handling that can modify the context at different stages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/plugins.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch, BetterFetchPlugin } from "@better-fetch/fetch";

const myPlugin = {
    id: "my-plugin",
    name: "My Plugin",
    hooks: {
        onRequest(context) {
        // do something with the context
        return context;
        },
        onResponse(context) {
            // do something with the context
            return context;
        },
        onError(context) {
            // do something with the context
        },
        onSuccess(context) {
            // do something with the context
        },
    }
} satisfies BetterFetchPlugin;

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com",
    plugins: [myPlugin],
});
```

