TITLE: Using Dynamic Parameters with Better Fetch in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use dynamic parameters in URL paths with the Better Fetch library. It shows how to create a fetch instance with a base URL and make requests with dynamic parameters using the ':' prefix in the URL path and providing values through the 'params' option.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/dynamic-parameters.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch } from "@better-fetch/fetch";

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "http://localhost:3000",
})

const res = await $fetch("/path/:id", {
    params: {
        id: "1"
    }
})

const res2 = await $fetch("/repos/:owner/:repo", {
    params: {
        owner: "octocat",
        repo: "hello-world"
    }
})
```

