TITLE: Exponential Backoff Retry Strategy in Better Fetch (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to implement an exponential backoff retry strategy in Better Fetch, specifying the number of attempts, base delay, and maximum delay.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/timeout-and-retry.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch } from "@better-fetch/fetch";

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "http://localhost:3000",
})
// ---cut---
const res = await $fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1", {
    retry: {
        count: 3,
        interval: 1000, //optional
    type: "exponential",
    attempts: 5,
    baseDelay: 1000, // Start with 1 second delay
    maxDelay: 10000 // Cap the delay at 10 seconds, so requests would go out after 1s then 2s, 4s, 8s, 10s
  }
});
```

