TITLE: Implementing onResponse Hook
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the implementation of the onResponse hook which handles the response after receiving it. This hook must return the response and has access to both response and request context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/hooks.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch } from "@better-fetch/fetch";

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "http://localhost:3000",
    onResponse(context) {        
        // do something with the context
        return context.response // return the response
    },
})
```

