TITLE: Implementing Success and Error Hooks
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement onSuccess and onError hooks that handle successful responses and errors respectively. These hooks receive the response context but don't return any values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/hooks.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch } from "@better-fetch/fetch";

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "http://localhost:3000",
    onSuccess(context) {
        // do something with the context
    },
    onError(context) {
        // do something with the context
    },
})
```

