TITLE: Defining Input Schema for Fetch in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define an input schema for a fetch request. When an input schema is defined, the request will use the POST method by default.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/fetch-schema.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch, createSchema } from "@better-fetch/fetch";
import { z } from "zod";

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com",
    schema: createSchema({
        "/path": {
            input: z.object({
                userId: z.string(),
                id: z.number(),
                title: z.string(),
                completed: z.boolean(),
            }),
        },
    }), 
})

const { data, error } = await $fetch("/path", {
    body: {}
})
```

