TITLE: Retry with Callback in Better Fetch (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to use a callback function with retry in Better Fetch. It logs a message each time a retry is attempted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bekacru/better-fetch/blob/main/doc/content/docs/timeout-and-retry.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createFetch } from "@better-fetch/fetch";

const $fetch = createFetch({
    baseURL: "http://localhost:3000",
})
// ---cut---
const res = await $fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1", {
  retry: 3,
  onRetry: (response) => {
    console.log(`Retrying request.`);
    }
});
```

